Class LoopTargetDetector.Detector

Enclosing class:
LoopTargetDetector
private final class LoopTargetDetector.Detector
extends EmptyBPLVisitor<java.lang.Object>

The visitor performing the actual loop target detection inside BoogiePL blocks.

Loop targets are always BPLVariableExpressions appearing in the BoogiePL AST, which show up in one of the following contexts:

  • As the target of a havoc command.
  • On the left hand side of an assignment command.
  • As the result variables of a procedure call command.
Therefore, this class only visits those parts of the AST and whenever a BPLVariableExpression is encountered, it is guaranteed to be a loop target.

Author:
Ovidio Mallo
